        "title": "URL validation takes too long",
        "body": "<p>I'm writing a Java program that queries a database, then takes all the URLs from the table and checks if the links work. I'm using the code below for validation.<\/p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>static boolean urlvalid(String theurl) throws IOException {\n    URL url = new URL(theurl);\n    HttpURLConnection http = (HttpURLConnection) url.openConnection()\n    Int statusCode = http.getResponseCode();\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>The issue is that this takes very long to run. It can check about 70 links per minute. How can I do this faster?<\/p>\n",
